COMMENTS: REDETERMINATION: 1 slide, voucher.  CTMcAllister-940529-13B.  Hematoxylin; permount. Locality: 3.2 km SW Shanno Hills. Host deposited in ASUMZ-19701.  NEW LOCALITY RECORD.  NOT M. monas.  Specimen flat, severely folded (right side), short ceca do not pass ovary, a postbifurcal gp, vitelline fields surpass ovary & a body type similar to M. lanceatum.  Specimen aso has shorter body & forebody lengths, smaller oral sucker & pharynx, smaller ovary, shorter egg size. M. lanceatum  has a longer body length, wider oral sucker, ventral sucker & phayrynx.  This specimen is frist report of a species wher ceca do not surpass ovary posteriorly, may be an undescribed species but will have to await additional museum quality specimen for description.  See Document 507 for more details.
